==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inweave
<hw>In*weave"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To weave in or
together; to intermix or intertwine by weaving; to interlace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Down they cast⟦br⟧
Their crowns, <qex>inwove</qex> with amaranth and gold.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inwheel</ent>⟦br⟧
